==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hemmer
<hw>Hem"mer</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who, or that
which, hems with a needle.</def> <specif>Specifically:</specif>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>An attachment to a sewing machine, for turning under
the edge of a piece of fabric, preparatory to stitching it down.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>A tool for turning over the edge of sheet metal to
make a hem.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>hemming-stitch</ent>⟦br⟧
